
[1]humorist

   HU'MORIST, n. One who conducts himself by his own inclination, or bent
   of mind; one who gratifies his own humor.

   The humorist is one that is greatly pleased or greatly displeased with
   little things; his actions seldom directed by the reason and nature of
   things.

   1. One that indulges humor in speaking or writing; one who has a
   playful fancy or genius.

   2. One who has odd conceits; also, a wag; a droll.
